<div class="intro">
<div class="welcome">
Welcome to ECS, the School  of Electronics and Computer Science at the University of Southampton. ECS is one of the world's leading centres for 
<a href="http://ia360911.us.archive.org:9090/wayback/20050224085840/http://www.ecs.soton.ac.uk/research/">research</a>, 
<a href="http://ia360911.us.archive.org:9090/wayback/20050224085840/http://www.ecs.soton.ac.uk/about/teaching/">teaching</a>, <a href="http://ia360911.us.archive.org:9090/wayback/20050224085840/http://www.ecs.soton.ac.uk/business/">enterprise and innovation</a> in Electronics, Electrical Engineering and Computer Science.
<div class="sig">Head of School: <a href="http://ia360911.us.archive.org:9090/wayback/20050224085840/http://www.ecs.soton.ac.uk/people/wh">Professor Wendy Hall</a></div>
</div>
<div class="headline"><a href="http://ia360911.us.archive.org:9090/wayback/20050224085840/http://www.ecs.soton.ac.uk/news/686"><img src="http://ia360911.us.archive.org:9090/wayback/20050224085840im_/http://www.ecs.soton.ac.uk/image.php?id=news_686_img&amp;maxw=200&amp;maxh=150&amp;corners=10&amp;edge=1&amp;checksum=93ae84aa7c64a4601f9b5058c06395d1&amp;fn=fn.png" alt="Zepler Building, Highfield Campus" title="Zepler Building, Highfield Campus (Copyright: Grantly Lynch)" border="0" width="200" height="130" class="thumbnail" /></a><h2>Headline News</h2><h3><a href="http://ia360911.us.archive.org:9090/wayback/20050224085840/http://www.ecs.soton.ac.uk/news/686">International meeting in Southampton could create worldwide OA policy</a></h3><p>A meeting of international institutions which have signed up to Open Access (OA) could result in a united policy creating a huge growth in free access to research findings. The Berlin 3 Open Access Meeting: Progress in Implementing the Berlin Declaration on Open Access to Knowledge in the Sciences and Humanities will be hosted next week by the University of Southampton.</p></div></div><div class='rightside'>

